title: For Sale:  Smith & Wesson 29-2 .44 Magnum 4-Inch Bbl...Near New...Mfd 1980
postcontent: Here's a very nice Smith & Wesson Model 29-2 double-action .44 Magnum. This revolver is built on the big square butt N-frame, wears the desirable 4" pinned barrel and has the counter-bored ("recessed") chambers. It features the white-outline adjustable rear sight, red ramp front sight, target hammer, target trigger, and smooth target stocks. This handsome revolver is factory finished in bright blue with color case hardened hammer and trigger. Condition is excellent with nearly all of the original finish remaining. There is a light cylinder turn line and a couple of very small handling marks. There is no rust or any pitting. The stocks are in fine shape but do show a little more handling wear than the revolver. The mechanics are in perfect working order with good timing and solid lock-up. The bore is excellent too with bright, sharp rifling. It's quite evident that this was a "safe queen" and saw only limited and careful use since new. According to the serial number, this beauty was manufactured in about 1980-82. A very nice revolver...they just don't make like this any longer!Buyer pays $20.00 shipping.

title: For Sale/Trade:  Rare 1970's Dan Wesson 15-2 .357 Magnum Revolver 6" barrel
postcontent: 1970's era (Either 1972, or 1978 I had 2 DW's and forget which this one is) Monson, Massachusetts Dan Wesson Model 15-2 .357 Magnum/.38 Special 6-shot Revolver with 6" barrel. The blueing is absolutely stunning; deep and dark. Original wood grips. Target adjustable rear sight. These revolver are capable of swapping the barrels for different lengths. Comes with barrel wrench to remove barrel as well as the feeler gauge to correctly space cyclinder gap. Shooting .38 special out of this feels like a .22. These revolvers are renown for their accuracy, as well as the amazing blue finish. Dan Wesson was the great-grandson of Daniel B Wesson of Smith&Wesson. He worked for the family business until they were bought out by a European company and then left to form Dan Wesson Arms and produced some of the finest revolvers ever made. The fitment of parts is amazing, strong cyclinder lockup. Selling to fund another project. Comes in MTM hard case. Full disclosure, there is a small knick on the bottom of the grip as well as a scratch in the wood, Otherwise this is in excellent condition. Looking to sell or trade ONLY for a Glock 19 Gen 4 +/- cash. Will not consider any other trades.Additional pictures available upon request

title: For Sale:  *IN STOCK*Brand New Rock Island M206 SPURLESS - 38 SPECIAL Conceal Carry 6 shot Revolver
postcontent: Don't forget to click on my Armslist store (towards the top right side of the posting).  I usually have close to 100 guns listed at very competitive prices.  Let's play "Who is the moron".  Here are your options:1. the idiot that lists on Armslist a used version of this firearm for $$$$ more than what I am asking for BNIB;2. the guy that pays that for the used one; or3. me for selling brand new fireams at such incredibly low prices.My wife picks #3 (but for totally unrelated reasons). This revolver reminds me of the Shay Model A convertibles that were sold in the 1980's through Ford dealers. They took modern mechanical features, and installed them in a 1920's looking Model A bodies. They were cool vintage looking cars, but with modern comfort and dependability (by 1980s standards). Rock Island has done basically the same trick with the M206 revolver. This revolver is HEAVILY inspired by the old Colt Detective revolvers that were the mainstay of undercover law enforcement through the 1970's. Gives you 6 shot capacity, and excepts Colt Detective speedloaders. features a "floating" frame mounted firing pin with a transfer bar safety similar to the Colt King Cobra. In the unlikely event the gun is dropped, this means it will not discharge until the trigger is squeezed. Other modern upgrades include replacing the Detective Special's leaf style hammer spring with a stronger coil spring. the frame is constructed out of 4140 ordnance grade steel. The double action trigger pull weight is fairly standard at 12- pounds, while single action breaks much lighter.A black oxide finish provides excellent durability and has been professionally applied.The M206 Spurless Revolver is ideal for self defense and concealed carry with a 2" fully shrouded barrel and spurless hammer, fixed front sight, and smooth channel frame cut rear sight. Includes both wood and rubber grips.  It is backed by a lifetime warranty from the manufacturer. Overall, the Rock Island 206 is a well priced, solidly built handgun designed to save your life in an emergency. Unloaded weight is 1.5lbs. rated for occassional + P use, but why would you use +p anyway? IMO much better gun then the offerings from Taurus and Rossi. I like it so much, I'm keeping one for myself.  Not quite the quality of a Smith and Wesson, but it doesn't cost anywhere near what a S&W will run you. Speed loaders are available for only $16.00, but only if purchased with the revolver.  Photo's look a little spotty due to thin coat of oil from the factory.  These are first quality guns.  All sales are final and "as is".  If you have any issue with the firearm you will need to address it with the manufacter/importer.  It is solely your responsibility to make certain that you can legally own the firearm where you reside.  All used/surplus firearms should be inspected by a gunsmith before firing.
